benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/invoicePayments/{paymentId}/customFields - Modify custom fields to payment

covered: Valid Request: TC01–TC04 cover successful updates with required and optional headers and various initial states, confirming 204 responses and persistence of changes.
Non-Existing Resource: TC06 confirms 404 when the payment is not found.
Authorization/Authentication: TC07 and TC11 cover missing/invalid authorization scenarios (400/401).
Error Handling & Validation: Tests TC05, TC08–TC13 cover invalid paymentId, missing/malformed body, invalid CustomField data, and security/server error cases (400/401/404/500).
Integration/Data Integrity: TC17 verifies data consistency by performing a GET after a PUT to confirm updated fields.
Performance/Edge Cases: TC14, TC15, TC19, TC20 cover large payloads, max-length values, concurrent requests, and overall performance considerations.
gaps: Partial Update Semantics: No explicit test asserts whether partial updates are allowed or rejected; ambiguous semantics remain.
403 Forbidden Coverage: Tests rely on 400/401; a dedicated 403 scenario is missing.
Caching/ETag Considerations: No tests for caching headers or conditional requests (ETag/If-None-Match).
Rate Limiting: No tests addressing rate limiting or throttling for PUT requests.
Stress/High-Load Concurrency: Concurrency covered by TC19 but lacks deeper stress scenarios to validate transactional integrity.
recommendations: Add a 403 Forbidden test to complement 401 Unauthorized and any role-based access control requirements.
Introduce a Partial Update semantics test to confirm or document whether partial field updates are allowed.
Add caching headers tests (ETag/Cache-Control) and conditional request handling if applicable, including 412 Precondition Failed scenarios.
Introduce rate-limiting tests to validate throttling behavior under bursts.
Extend concurrency testing with higher load or race-condition scenarios to assess transactional integrity under stress.
Optionally add a 409 Conflict test for duplicate CustomField identifiers and ensure consistent GET results.
